On Mon, 11 Feb 2002, Robert S. Whitaker wrote:

> I also pulled the engine from my '71 bus and I had the Bentley manual and
> the "How to Rebuild Your VW Engine. . " book close at hand. I was
surprised
> when I read in the Bentley manual that on the '71 bus ONLY 3 BOLTS HOLD
THE
> ENGINE TO THE TRANSMISSION! The "How to Rebuild. . ." book said that the
> upper left bolt had to be removed from underneath. This is the same bolt
not
> referenced by the Bentley manual - apparently the one that is not needed?


> Since the books seem to contradict each other, which one is correct? Does
a
> stock '71 only need 3 bolts? If so I'd like to leave the upper left off
due

I always had all four in my 71 IIRC and I have always felt like a VW
engine wasn't held in tight enough for my nervous self. (no never had one
fall out)  so I would be anal about putting in all four, but the right
size and yes they are a relatively minor PITA to get in and out.

Bob



